member.name: IEnumTfDisplayAttributeInfo.Clone
member.summary: Creates a copy of the enumerator object.
member.param: Pointer to an interface pointer that receives the new enumerator.

returns.para: This method can return one of these values.

member.name: IEnumTfDisplayAttributeInfo.Next
member.summary: Obtains, from the current position, the specified number of elements in the enumeration sequence.
member.param: Specifies the number of elements to obtain.
Pointer to an array of interface pointers that receives the requested objects. This array must be at least ulCount elements in size.
Pointer to a ULONG value that receives the number of elements actually obtained. The number of elements can be less than the number of items requested. This parameter can be NULL.

returns.para: This method can return one of these values.

listheader.description: The method reached the end of the enumeration before the specified number of elements were obtained.

member.name: IEnumTfDisplayAttributeInfo.Reset
member.summary: Resets the enumerator object by moving the current position to the beginning of the enumeration sequence.

returns.para: This method can return one of these values.

member.name: IEnumTfDisplayAttributeInfo.Skip
member.summary: Moves the current position forward in the enumeration sequence by the specified number of elements.
member.param: Contains the number of elements to skip.

returns.para: This method can return one of these values.

listheader.description: The method reached the end of the enumeration before the specified number of elements could be skipped.

member.name: IEnumTfDisplayAttributeInfo
member.summary: The IEnumTfDisplayAttributeInfo interface is implemented by the TSF manager to provide an enumeration of display attribute information objects.
